post_text:
We would like to thank everyone for the support we have received over the past few weeks! Whether it was a curbside order, words of encouragement, or just liking our posts! The community that surrounds this public house is incredible! We appreciate every single one of you!

Thank you to our dedicated staff for becoming essential and helping us navigate the transition from a bustling little pub to a take out and delivery!

After tonight we will be taking a break from take-out and delivery. This is our opportunity to rest and reset. While we are closed we will be dreaming up fun and exciting things for when we re-open. We have a lot of things in store... Stay tuned!

Please be safe and stay well!

#JKPH #josiekellyspublichouse #josiekellys #josiekellys2go #curbsidekindalife #publife #teamJKPH

Bring Paint Night at Josie Kelly's home! Handlaget shop in Ocean City is bringing us a Curbside kit so we all make something beautiful! Ka la Hiki Ola is Hawaiian for The dawning of a new day. It speaks to optimism, hope and promise.

This $26 Curbside Paint Night kit comes complete with everything you need to create your own art work. Follow along at your leisure with Christine Boardman and her detailed instructions.

Kit includes: reclaimed wood approximately 10√ó12, a rub on word stencil, 2 paint colors, applicators, and coordinating rub on image transfers and sealant. (Each project will be unique, have different transfers and colors that coordinate with the transfers.)

Paints are non-toxic, zero voc chalk paints made by Wise Owl. Great for working indoors. The transfers are made by Redesign with Prima. This is a great introductory project to get familiar with chalk paints and transfers. You can use these new skills to work on larger projects such as furniture.

Call 609-904-6485 to reserve your kit or order online at toasttab.com/josie-kellys/v3

What an honor, in the company of so many incredible local bars. A huge thank you to our amazing team and all of our loyal customers!
